    <p>
        In the construction of mathematical models (especially in the biological sciences and engineering), it can happen that one or more coefficients in a differential equation is a piecewise-defined function.
        In particular, when either <m>P(x)</m> or <m>f(x)</m> is a piecewise-defined function, the equation is then referred to as a <alert>piecewise-linear differential equation</alert>.
    </p>

