    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
                Find the general solution to the following differential equations.
                Determine whether there are any transient terms in the solution and give the largest interval <m>I</m> over which the general solution is defined.
            </p>

            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>3\dfrac{dy}{dx}+15y=5</m>
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>y'=4y+x^{2}+7</m>
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>(1+x)\dfrac{dy}{dx}-xy=x+x^{2}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>\cos^{2}(x)\sin(x)\dfrac{dy}{dx}+(\cos^{3}(x))y=1</m>
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>\dfrac{dP}{dt}+2tP=P+6t-3</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </li>

        <li>
            <p>
